<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-10T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-10T17:00:00-05:00" n="34" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/1595: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-10T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            10, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Press despatch from Havana printed in New York <hi rend="italic">Sun</hi> today states that you have issued a statement to the
                                effect that United States Government would not supervise the coming
                                elections in Cuba.</p>
                            <pb facs="0169" n="84" xml:id="pg_84"/>
                            <p>In view of the fact that you asked instructions of the Department in
                                this matter which were issued in Department’s telegram of December
                                8, 1 p.m., I am reluctant to believe that this press report is
                                accurate.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>